== a bare paren glued to the name completes the file:
'report(1).log'
== a bare open paren keeps the filesystem context:
'report(1).log'
'report(2).log'
== a backslash-escaped paren completes the file:
'report(1).log'
== a double-quoted paren completes the file:
report(1).log
report(2).log
== a single-quoted paren completes the file:
report(1).log
report(2).log
